subsection.p:
We can verify that the two equations in  are actually equivalent by solving the second equation for y in terms of x.
	6x-3y \amp = -6 \amp\amp \blert{\text{Add}~3y~\text{and 6 to both sides.}}
        6x+6 \amp = 3y \amp\amp \blert{\text{Divide both sides by 3.}}
        2x+2 \amp = y            
The second equation is the same as the first equation. A system in which the two equations are equivalent is called dependentsystem of equationsdependentdependent system of equations
. A dependent system has infinitely many solutions: Every point on the graph is a solution to the system.

